Garba Shehu – The Presidency on Tuesday has reacted to reports that President Muhammadu Buhari has appointed a new Chief of Staff, CoS. READ ALSO:  Emir of Ilorin hails Gambari’s appointment as Buhari’s new Chief of Staff According to reports on social media,  Buhari appointed Prof. Ibrahim Gambari as his new CoS, following the demise of Abba Kyari. In an exclusive interview with Daily post, Buhari’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, the presidential spokesperson said he was not aware of such development.In a text sent, Garba wrote: “I have not been briefed.”